Message.MsgText: ADMN0039E=ADMN0039E: The specified connection definition (Connection factory interface = {0} ) does not exist under the specified resource adapter.
Message.Explanation: No connection definition exists for the specified resource adapter.
Message.UserResponse: Verify that the specified connection definition is correct. It might belong to another resource adapter. Check the ra.xml file.

Message.MsgText: ADMN0003E=ADMN0003E: The service is unable to load a document type definition (DTD) file {0}.
Message.Explanation: The system cannot find the DTD file that is associated with the MBean descriptor file.
Message.UserResponse: Verify the corresponding DTD file is in the class path.

Message.MsgText: ADMN1001I=ADMN1001I: An attempt is made to launch {0} on node {1}.
Message.Explanation: This action is an audit of an attempted process launch. The user ID is not available because security is not enabled.
Message.UserResponse: No user action is required.

Message.MsgText: ADMN0042E=ADMN0042E: The AdminObject value is not specified.
Message.Explanation: A Java 2 Connector (J2C) architecture connection factory cannot be created because the AdminObject value was not specified.
Message.UserResponse: Specify the AdminObject name that is defined in the resource adapter.

Message.MsgText: ADMN1212E=ADMN1212E: Internal Error: MBean proxy unable process method {0} for interface {1}
Message.Explanation: The MBean proxy is unable to process the method.
Message.UserResponse: Contact support.

Message.MsgText: ADMN0038E=ADMN0038E: The service failed to save the resource adapter to assign object IDs. The exception is {0}
Message.Explanation: The service failed to save the resource adapter to assign object IDs.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: ADMN0002E=ADMN0002E: {0} is not a valid visibility value, which must be an integer within the range of 1 to 4 (inclusive).
Message.Explanation: An incorrect visibility value is specified.
Message.UserResponse: Specify a visibility value as an integer between 1 and 4, inclusive.

Message.MsgText: ADMN1000I=ADMN1000I: An attempt is made to launch {0} on node {1}. (User ID = {2})
Message.Explanation: This action is an audit of an attempted process launch by the specified user.
Message.UserResponse: No user action is required.

Message.MsgText: ADMN0037W=ADMN0037W: The {0} operation "{1}" is deprecated. {2}
Message.Explanation: This operation will be removed in a future release.
Message.UserResponse: Update the code that uses this operation to use a non-deprecated attribute or operation.

Message.MsgText: ADMN0001W=ADMN0001W: The service is unable to parse the MBean descriptor file {0}.
Message.Explanation: A parsing error occurs when the administrative code tries to read the MBean descriptor file.
Message.UserResponse: Find XML grammar errors for the MBean descriptor file in question and correct them.

Message.MsgText: ADMN0041E=ADMN0041E: The specified AdminObject name (AdminObjectClass name = {0}) does not exist under the specified resource adapter.
Message.Explanation: The specified AdminObject name does not exist for the specified resource adapter.
Message.UserResponse: Verify that the specified AdminObject name is correct. It might belong to another resource adapter. Check the ra.xml file.

Message.MsgText: ADMN1211E=ADMN1211E: Unable to open connector to admin agent while processing method {0} for interface {1}
Message.Explanation: The admin agent must be started and reachable by the application server.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the admin agent is started and the application server discovers the admin agent.

Message.MsgText: ADMN1103E=ADMN1103E: For extension point {0} the extension class {1} failed to load
Message.Explanation: The extension class file might be missing from the module, or the file might not be properly defined in the plugin.xml file of the module.
Message.UserResponse: Verify that the extension is properly defined and that the implementation class is in the module.

Message.MsgText: ADMN0036W=ADMN0036W: The {0} attribute "{1}" is deprecated. {2}
Message.Explanation: This attribute will be removed in a future release.
Message.UserResponse: Update the code that uses this attribute to use a non-deprecated attribute or operation.

Message.MsgText: ADMN0040E=ADMN0040E: The connection definition is not specified.
Message.Explanation: A Java 2 Connector (J2C) architecture connection factory cannot be created because the connection definition was not specified.
Message.UserResponse: Specify the connection definition that is defined in the resource adapter.

Message.MsgText: ADMN1210I=ADMN1210I: Check the System Log for information on the System Dump
Message.Explanation: Location of System Dump or errors appear in the System Log
Message.UserResponse: Check for the IEA911E message in the System Log for location of a successful dump operation.

Message.MsgText: ADMN1102E=ADMN1102E: The product or feature ({0}) version of the Deployment Manager ({1}) is earlier than that of this node ({2}); the node has not been added
Message.Explanation: The node was not added to the cell. The product does not support the deployment manager being at an earlier product version than the node.
Message.UserResponse: Upgrade the deployment manager to the same or later version as that of the node.

Message.MsgText: ADMN0035W=ADMN0035W: The system clock of node {0} is not synchronized with that of the deployment manager.
Message.Explanation: If the system clocks on the deployment manager and a node is not synchronized closely enough, the operations involving the node might fail when security is enabled.
Message.UserResponse: Set the systems clocks to within at least a few minutes of each other.

Message.MsgText: ADMN1101I=ADMN1101I: Beginning attempt to federate a node with WebSphere version {0} to a cell controlled by dmgr at version {1}, or to remove such a node from the cell.
Message.Explanation: The process of adding a node to a cell, or removing a node from a cell, was begun.
Message.UserResponse: No user action is required.
